This paper is about using convolutional neural networks for biomedical image segmentation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of data augmentation and end-to-end training, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper specifically focuses on biomedical imaging, which could also fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
